    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="337"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.35112 RP/8–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-08T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1051. Emb may authorize or license Arg, US, UK and other satisfactory firms,
                    write expired or canceled insurance for Axis firms which are in process
                    liquidation or nationalization and which are under control Arg liquidating
                    committee. (Ur 1753, Aug 3, 1778, Aug 6<note n="41" xml:id="d337fn41">Latter not
                        printed.</note>). Policies and authorization should be subject cancellation
                    in event liquidation or nationalization not accomplished within specified period
                    (ur 1364, June 28<note n="42" xml:id="d337fn42">Not printed.</note>). Brit
                    referring to London anticipate concurrence.</p>
                <p>Such insurance unlike general licensing (ur 1364) and trademarks (ur 1707, July
                    31) considered separable from Replacement. Denial insurance PL firms under
                    urgent consideration. Cable follows.</p>
                <p>Emb should in so far as possible avoid taking affirmative action re replacement
                    program which might seem inconsistent with possible claim to Ger assets in Arg
                    by Allied Control Commission. It is hoped definite decision can be reached
                    soon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
